Commentary Text: Umesh Yadav to Warner, out Caught by Rahane at deep mid-wicket!! Warner falls!! KKR are now storming their way back into this game in these end overs. Slower ball on that hard length outside off, Warner doesn't time the pull well enough and it's taken comfortably at deep mid-wicket. Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to Umesh Yadav, out Caught&Bowled!! Kuldeep has a fourth. And he's done it all alone. He's flighted up a googly, drawn the top-edge on Umesh's slog-sweep, and then called for it himself. The ball's high into the sky, ballooning away towards mid-on. But Kuldeep running. He's running some more. And then in the end he's diving as well to pluck it out. Things avenging the last two years makes you do! It's a pity he can't go for a hat-trick. Umesh Yadav c and b Kuldeep Yadav 0(1)

Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Rahane, no run, and this time Rahane reviews against an LBW decision. What a start this! A clear inside edge and Rahane is safe again. Was on a length around off and it shaped back slightly as Rahane got an inside edge that deflected on to the pads. Not impressive umpiring by Madangopal this

Commentary Text: Mustafizur to Rahane, no run, Rahane has been given out caught behind. And he has decided to opt for DRS. Think this might have just brushed the top of his right pad. Yes, nothing on UltraEdge when the ball is next to bat. And the decision has to be overturned. Was on a length around off and it shaped back in to beat Rahane's defence, flicking his back pad as it flew to the keeper. DRS comes to Rahane's rescue
